definitions.definition: Any plant of the genus Plantago , with a rosette of sessile leaves about 10 cm (4") long with a narrow part instead of a petiole , and with a spike inflorescence with the flower spacing varying widely among the species. See also psyllium .

main_definition: Any plant of the genus Plantago , with a rosette of sessile leaves about 10 cm (4") long with a narrow part instead of a petiole , and with a spike inflorescence with the flower spacing varying widely among the species. See also psyllium .

definitions.definition: A plant in the genus Musa , the genus that includes banana , but with lower sugar content than banana.
The fruit of the plant, usually cooked before eating and used like potatoes.
